						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into a wall of Bīradēva temple.</p>						

						<p>1625-26 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1547, Krōdhana, daśami, Saturday. The details cannot be verified. The Śaka year corresponds to 1625-26 A.D. </p>						

						<p>It records the construction of the Chandraśālā by Nāgaṇṇa-gauḍa, son of Bhūsaṇṇa-gauḍa of Koṇaganūr.</p>						

						</summary>
